ENTRY       EC 1.14.13.90               Enzyme
NAME        zeaxanthin epoxidase;
            Zea-epoxidase
CLASS       Oxidoreductases;
            Acting on paired donors, with incorporation or reduction of molecular oxygen;
            With NADH or NADPH as one donor, and incorporation of one atom of oxygen into the other donor
SYSNAME     zeaxanthin,NAD(P)H:oxygen oxidoreductase
REACTION    zeaxanthin + 2 NAD(P)H + 2 H+ + 2 O2 = violaxanthin + 2 NAD(P)+ + 2 H2O (overall reaction) [RN:R10070 R10071];
            (1a) zeaxanthin + NAD(P)H + H+ + O2 = antheraxanthin + NAD(P)+ + H2O [RN:R06946 R07199];
            (1b) antheraxanthin + NAD(P)H + H+ + O2 = violaxanthin + NAD(P)+ + H2O [RN:R06947 R07200]
ALL_REAC    R06946 R06947 R07199 R07200 R10070 R10071
SUBSTRATE   zeaxanthin [CPD:C06098];
            NADH [CPD:C00004];
            NADPH [CPD:C00005];
            H+ [CPD:C00080];
            O2 [CPD:C00007];
            antheraxanthin [CPD:C08579]
PRODUCT     violaxanthin [CPD:C08614];
            NAD+ [CPD:C00003];
            NADP+ [CPD:C00006];
            H2O [CPD:C00001];
            antheraxanthin [CPD:C08579]
COMMENT     A flavoprotein (FAD) that is active under conditions of low light. Along with EC 1.10.99.3, violaxanthin de-epoxidase, this enzyme forms part of the xanthophyll (or violaxanthin) cycle, which is involved in protecting the plant against damage by excess light. It will also epoxidize lutein in some higher-plant species.
